


this is using the modern version of react
In order to switch on company computer, I'm using NVM, node version manager

nvm is tricky in that the terminal forget I can use it
if I try to reinstall nvm with:
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.3/install.sh | bash
it will then remember that it has it installed.

DO NOT close terminal like it recommends.
it gives two commands you can run to use nvm without closing terminal
run those two commands and you can now use nvm.

if you close that terminal window, you must run the curl install again


to switch to most up to date version, use command:
nvm use 24.11.1

then do
npm run dev

